
[1]scaly

   SCA'LY, a. [from scale.]

   1. Covered or abounding with scales; rough; as a scaly fish; the scaly
   crocodile.

   2. Resembling scales, lamina or layers.

   3. In botany, composed of scales lying over each other, as a scaly
   bulb; having scales scattered over it, as a scaly stem.
